User's guide in french

Allow several backups per day

Secure parsing of directories.conf
If a dir/file to exclude doesn't exist, do not take it in account in 
DirConf#@filesToExclude and log it level ERROR. Same for the dir/file to add.
Si on oublie le +/- le chemin est ignoré dans la sauvegarde et log de niveau ERROR.
Si le chemin ne comporte pas le / initial, celui-ci sera ajouté automatiquement,
et sera loggé au niveau ERROR.
Et si le chemin comporte un / final ?

Catch the unknow options from command line.

Allow automatic remove of old backups (more than X days)
But always keep a minimum of X backups

Recovery

Argument for log on the command line ('daily', 'weekly' or 'monthly')

Log file should only show us ERROR and FATAL in a production environment.
That must be the default beahviour. So we need an option to log all levels
during tests/developpment.
